discussion_comments.comment_body:
I think we should generally implement this a bit differently, flow-wise:

- first, look up the `cachedData`
- if it's undefined
  - return fetch
- else 
  - check if that data is stale
  - if it is - trigger a background refetch
  - in any case, return it

```
const cachedData = this.getQueryData<TData>(options.queryKey)

if (cachedData === undefined) {
  return this.fetchQuery(options)
}

const defaultedOptions = this.defaultQueryOptions(options)
if (query.isStaleByTime(defaultedOptions.staleTime)) {
  void this.prefetchQuery(defaultedOptions)
}

return cachedData
```

calling `prefetchQuery` instead of `query.fetch` is important because:

- it catches errors that happen during fetching, which is what we want for a background refetch
- it goes through `fetchQuery`, which turns off retries, which is also what we want:

https://github.com/TanStack/query/blob/bdd2b552d3647242e45c85f4c765fd293862d6d5/packages/query-core/src/queryClient.ts#L329-L331

